【0】Highlights from the Current Issue – Audiovisual Summary
Dr Thomas Gerber, Associate Editor for _Mayo Clinic Proceedings_ , discusses the articles featured on the cover page of the September 2013 issue.

【1】These include:

【2】**“Immediate Open Repair vs Surveillance in Patients With Small Abdominal Aortic Aneurysms: Survival Differences by Aneurysm Size,”**

【3】by Dr Giovanni Filardo and colleagues;

【4】**“Abdominal Aortic Aneurysm Size: The Effect of Treatment vs Observation on Outcome,”**

【5】by Dr Peter Gloviczki;

【6】**“Role of Dietary Salt and Potassium Intake in Cardiovascular Health and Disease: A Review of the Evidence,”**

【7】by Ms Kristal J. Aaron and Dr Paul W. Sanders;

【8】**“Software-Guided Insulin Dosing: Tight Glycemic Control and Decreased Glycemic Derangements in Critically Ill Patients,”**

【9】by Dr Nicole M. Saur and colleagues;

【10】**“Association of Dysglcemia and All-Cause Mortality Across the Spectrum of Coronary Artery Disease,”**

【11】by Dr Shi-Wei Yang and colleagues;

【12】**“Improvements in Our Understanding of Diabetes Mellitus,”**

【13】by Dr Irl B. Hirsch;

【14】**“Willis-Ekbom Disease Foundation Revised Consensus Statement on the Management of Restless Legs Syndrome,”**

【15】by Dr Michael H. Silber and colleagues;

【16】**“Hospitalizations and Emergency Department Use in Mayo Clinic Biobank Participants Within the Employee and Community Health Medical Home,”**

【17】by Dr Paul Y. Takahashi and colleagues;

【18】**“The Mayo Clinic Biobank: A Building Block for Individualized Medicine,”**

【19】by Dr Janet E. Olson and colleagues;

【20】**“Female Athlete Triad and Its Components: Toward Improved Screening and Management,”**

【21】by Dr Asma Javed and colleagues;

【22】**“Wound Healing: A Paradigm for Regeneration,”**

【23】by Dr Victor W. Wong and colleagues; and

【24】**“Preprocedural Considerations in Gastrointestinal Endoscopy,”**

【25】by Drs Emmanuel C. Gorospe and Amy S. Oxentenko
